	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Oct 22nd 6:08 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><br>I was considering joining a raid in Nagafen's Lair (Solusek B?) scheduled to happen after the next patch update (Tues., Oct. 23rd) of the world servers (my main's on the Seventh Hammer world server)<br><br>I happen not to be in any of the guilds hosting the raid.&nbsp;&nbsp;Anywho - I posted on a server-related website that I wanted to join in on the raid along with my current resistances (none in the triple digits; the highest one being seventy-some (probably due to Ry'gorr armor pieces)).  One of the persons co-ordinating the raid noted that I'd be 'eaten in about a minute by the AoE roar (even for Nagafen) ... (I) need to work on those resists - especially at 47.<br><br>I found this terribly disconcerting.  I play one (1) character in EverQuest (maybe that's a mistake in and of itself!) since February and now I'm not even worth joining in on raids.  Of course, after thinking about it this morning, it made since.  Obviously, most things don't even become mildly effective until the one-hundreds and... well, I'm sure you can figure out how I added up the math.<br><br>I have two (2) questions --<br><br><br>1.) Obviously, does this mean that all the top-level guilds on most servers are those that a) have guild jewelers that b) build resist. gear that c) peeps can use on guild raids again fiends like Naggy, et cetera?<br><br>2.) Is there any resist gear that a paladin can wear without taking _HUGE_ drops in his AC, et cetera.  I could switch out a Deepwater Helm for a Crown of the Froglok Kings and the Ry'Gorr Chain Collar for a Necklace of Superiority with the resulting fifteen AC drop but an additional twenty-five fire resist and cold resist? <br><br>3.) Why as a paladin do I always feel like a walking inventory and it I have the wrong item on hand that I'm gonna get smacked upside the head for it?<br><br><br>That doesn't even go into the 'where the heck am I going to get all this platinum from' issue to _BUY_ these things, obviously since I can't hunt them down at this stage of the game.  And I'm 47. '=(  I would mention trading out my Cloak of the Ice Bear for a Cloak of Flame but isn't that what one would be going on such a raid to get?<br><br>As a side note, if I can't get help from my guild and friends with these things, should I look for a new guild and different friends? Would that make me a terrible paladin?<br><br>P.S.: I know there are a number of questions in this post.  Sorry.<br><br>P.P.S.: I'm on a rant... I probably don't mean to be as harsh as I may sound. Sorry (again about that).<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
