	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 23rd 10:14 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.95]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Greetings Elysius and welcome to the higher-end game!<br><br>I learned, at about the same time you are learning now, that resistance gear was ALL important when considering certain encounters...Dragons definitely being one of them.&nbsp;&nbsp;When going up against someone like Nagafen, Wuoshi, Trakanon, Gorenaire, Vox, Severilous, Ragefire, or any other Dragon...resistance is the key to success. It has very little or even nothing to do with AC...unless you are selected to main tank the mob.<br><br>When I go into the Halls of Testing in the Temple of Veeshan, I do everything in my power to boost my cold and heat resistances. Yes, I lose about 100 AC pts right now due to the gear I have, (I'm working on it!) but if I'm getting melee attacked by the mob then we are in trouble anyway. The main tanks should be able to hold his aggro.  So the only thing hitting me, other than the occasional Riposte, are the AoE spells (heat and cold...depending) cast by the mob and the AoE Breath Weapon that goes off every 15 seconds or so. Consequently, Resistance gear is the key to my health and continued ability to do damage to the mob...not to mention save mana for the Clerics.<br><br>Since I am still only level 52 and still going up against Nagafen in an attempt to get my burnt book for my epic, I worry about 2 things and 2 things only when preparing to face him: Magic Resistance and Heat Resistance. AC matters very little.  Magic Resistance keeps you from fleeing in fear everytime he roars. The Heat Resistance obviously protects you from his Breath Weapon which can routinely hit for 500.<br><br>When facing Naggy, I put on the Froglock Crown and my old Dwarven Ringmail Tunic (That's right...the one from CRUSH that I wore at level 10 that costs less than 20 plat!) I use my Crested Mistmoore Shield for the saves and put on all my resistance jewelry.  I put on my Bloodstained Mantle with it's +10 save to Magic (That's right...the one I got in Unrest in my 20's) and any other piece I can think of that will boost my Fire/Magic saves.<br><br>My advice would be to do some searches for gear you can wear that can boost your saves on Fire/Cold/Magic. You will be surprised that a lot of nice pieces are not very expensive.  The Bloodstained Mantle cost about 30 plat...maybe less. You already have a very nice Cloak of the Ice Bear with it's +20 save on cold. If short on cash, look into a Kunzar Cloak (+10 save on Heat) that should cost about 100 plat and are often left to rot in Karnor's Castle.  A +14 Magic Jascinth Ring should cost less than 500 plat and specific AC 4/+10 Cold/Fire rings are not very expensive.<br><br>You can acquire the more expensive resistance gear as you level, now that you know it is important. Those items include such things as the Blue Diamond Bracer, The Diamond Wedding Ring, Gold Diamond Mask, Crown of the Froglock Kings, Electrum Blue Diamond Earring, and any host of various magical armor items and weapons.<br><br>Good luck!!<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>52nd Dwarven Cavalier<br>In Service to Power of the Ages<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></tr>
